## Key Commands

```bash
# ─── Workspace management ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
make setup          # First-time setup: install tools, clone repos
make update         # Pull all repos + re-sync AI configs
make sync-ai        # Push AI configs from ai/ → all active repos
make check          # Verify env health: tools, env vars, repo access
make status         # Git status across all production repos
make lint           # Lint all Python repos (ruff + mypy)
make test           # Run pytest across all Python repos

# ─── Environment activation ───────────────────────────────────────────────
source activate.sh && source ~/.iron/env.local

# ─── Development (from repo roots) ────────────────────────────────────────
uv run pytest tests/ -v
uv run ruff check .
uv run mypy . --ignore-missing-imports
sqlfluff lint dbt-framework/models/ --dialect databricks
terraform fmt -check -recursive
pre-commit run --all-files

# ─── IronLayer CLI ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ironlayer plan          # Generate validated execution plan
ironlayer diff          # Schema / data diff
ironlayer lineage       # Lineage query
ironlayer status        # System health check

# ─── IronPilot CLI ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ironpilot review code <path>       # AI code review (local first)
ironpilot agent run --item <ID>    # Run backlog item interactively
ironpilot agent run --next         # Run highest-priority item
ironpilot ai-usage                 # Track Anthropic spend
ironpilot monitor schema           # Check bronze table schema drift
```

## AI Configuration — Single Source of Truth

**CRITICAL: Never edit AI configs directly in individual repos.**
Always edit in `ai/cursor/rules/`, `ai/claude/skills/`, etc., then run `make sync-ai`.

```
ai/cursor/rules/          → synced to .cursor/rules/ in all active repos
ai/cursor/skills/         → synced to .cursor/skills/ in all active repos
ai/cursor/mcp.json.template → synced to .cursor/mcp.json in all active repos
ai/claude/CLAUDE.md       → synced to CLAUDE.md in all active repos
ai/claude/skills/         → synced to .claude/skills/ in all active repos
ai/shared/AGENTS.md       → synced to AGENTS.md in all active repos
```

## Repo-Specific Overrides

Each repo can have a `local-rules/` directory with overrides NOT managed by sync.
Use for repo-specific conventions that don't apply workspace-wide.

## Version Management

- Workspace version: `workspace.yml` (semver — bump when standards change)
- Tool versions: `.tool-versions` (mise pins — all developers use same versions)
- Product versions: semver tags in each product repo

## Environment Setup

Credentials live in `~/.iron/env.local` (never commit). Template: `tooling/env/env.template`.

- **Load:** `source ~/.iron/env.local` or use `source activate.sh` (loads env + sets WORKSPACE_ROOT, PYTHONPATH)
- **direnv:** Each repo has `.envrc` that auto-sources env when you `cd` in. Run `direnv allow` in workspace and each repo after `make setup`
- **Verify:** `make check-env` validates required vars; `make check` runs full health check (includes check-env)

Key env vars: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `DATABRICKS_HOST`, `DATABRICKS_TOKEN`, `GITHUB_TOKEN`, `IRON_BUDGET_LIMIT`, `VLLM_BASE_URL`
